1. URLValidator regex (lines 96-98): Nested quantifiers in the host_re pattern with alternation causing catastrophic backtracking potential when processing malformed URLs with repeated characters in the hostname section.

2. EmailValidator user_regex (lines 179-182): Nested quantifiers in the dot-atom pattern with repeated character classes and alternation, vulnerable to ReDoS when processing specially crafted email addresses with repeated characters in the local part.

3. validate_domain_part method (line 227): Domain validation using domain_regex with nested quantifiers and alternation patterns that can cause exponential backtracking on crafted domain inputs.

All three vulnerabilities involve nested quantifiers with alternation that can lead to catastrophic backtracking when processing untrusted input, potentially causing denial of service through CPU exhaustion.
